OL,3,CWho was Donald Campbell, Bluebird's
OL,4,Cfamous pilot?
OL,6,FBut who was Donald Campbell, a man
OL,7,Fwhose name has become synonymous with
OL,8,FConiston in the decades since the
OL,9,Ffatal accident?
OL,11,FWho was Donald Campbell?
OL,13,FThe son of Sir Malcolm Campbell, the
OL,14,Fcharismatic and patriotic Donald was
OL,15,Fdestined to follow in his father's
OL,16,Ffootsteps. His father was a world
OL,17,Fspeed record holder on land and water.
OL,18,FSir Malcolm was one of the few record
OL,19,Fbreakers of his era to die of natural
OL,20,Fcauses rather than in a crash.
